In his remarks, Vice President Mike Pence thanks the audience and conveys greetings from President Donald Trump. He highlights the achievements of the Trump administration in the first three years, including rebuilding the military, tax cuts, deregulation, and job creation. Pence emphasizes the administration's response to the coronavirus pandemic and promises to ensure that states and healthcare workers have the necessary supplies and resources. He contrasts the Trump administration's agenda with that of Joe Biden, stating that Biden's policies would lead to socialism and decline. Pence discusses various policy areas such as taxes, regulations, trade, energy, healthcare, and immigration, highlighting the differences between the two candidates. He concludes by emphasizing the importance of freedom and faith in America and urging Americans to choose the path of freedom and opportunity in the upcoming election.